    <p>Pre­ci­sion man­u­fac­turer Broad­way In­dus­trial Group has re­ceived a bind­ing let­ter of in­tent (LOI) from Sek­sun Tech­nol­ogy (Suzhou), which is of­fer­ing US$50 mil­lion (S$67 mil­lion) to buy the for­mer’s hard disk drive busi­ness.</p>
    <p>In­cor­po­rated in China, Sek­sun Tech­nol­ogy (Suzhou)’s core com­pe­ten­cies are in pre­ci­sion metal stamp­ing.</p>
    <p>Un­der the LOI, the buyer will ac­quire sub­stan­tially all as­sets used in Broad­way In­dus­trial’s ac­tu­a­tor arm and re­lated parts man­u­fac­tur­ing oper­a­tions.</p>


